'''Vladimír Darida''' ({{IPA|cs|ˈvlaɟɪmiːr ˈdarɪda}}; born 8 August 1990) is a Czech professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[central midfielder]] for [[Czech First League]] club [[FC Hradec Králové|Hradec Králové]] and for the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]].

==Club career==
===Early football career in the Czech Republic===
Born in [[Plzeň]], Darida came through at [[Viktoria Plzeň]] whilst also spending time on loan at [[FK Baník Sokolov]] in 2011.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Adam|last=Kadlec|title=Seriál FP čeští talenti: Plzeňský štírek Darida, Jiráčkův nástupce|url=https://www.fotbalportal.cz/ostatni/vse/28624-serial-fp-cesti-talenti-plzensky-stirek-darida-jirackuv-nastupce/|website=Fotbal Portal|date=22 March 2011|access-date=14 December 2022|language=cs}}</ref>

===SC Freiburg===
In late summer 2013, Darida transferred to [[SC Freiburg]] for a transfer fee reported as four million Euros,<ref>{{Cite news|title=Hotovo, Darida přestupuje z Plzně do Freiburgu|url=http://www.eurofotbal.cz/clanky/hotovo-darida-prestupuje-z-plzne-do-freiburgu-229552/|url-status=dead|website=Eurofotbal|date=29 October 2013|language=cs|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029193538/http://www.eurofotbal.cz/clanky/hotovo-darida-prestupuje-z-plzne-do-freiburgu-229552/|archive-date=29 October 2013}}</ref> joining up with his compatriots [[Pavel Krmaš]] and [[Václav Pilař]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Vladimír Darida přestupuje do Freiburgu|url=https://fcviktoria.cz/clanek.asp?id=Vladimir-Darida-prestupuje-do-Freiburgu-8164|website=Viktoria Plzeň|date=29 August 2012|access-date=14 December 2022|language=cs}}</ref> According to Viktoria Plzeň owner Tomáš Paclík, Freiburg paid 6.2 million Euros for Darida and a 30% share of the next transfer.<ref>{{Cite news|first=David|last=Janeczek|title=Podle nového formátu se hrát nemusí. Se sledovaností na O2 TV si lžeme do kapsy, přednášel Paclík|url=https://sport.aktualne.cz/fotbal/ceska-liga/tomas-paclik-na-vse/r~eac583f0fe8511e68af8002590604f2e/|website=Aktualně.cz|publisher=[[Economia]]|date=2 March 2017|language=cs}}</ref>

On 24 October 2013, Darida debuted for SC Freiburg in the [[2013–14 UEFA Europa League]] group stage match against [[G.D. Estoril Praia|Estoril Praia]], scoring a goal in the 11th minute which ended in a 1–1  draw.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Darida ozdobil debut za Freiburg gólem, v pohárech skóroval i Kadlec|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/pohary/darida-skoroval-v-evropske-lize-za-freiburg.A131024_212525_fot_pohary_vl|website=[[Mladá fronta Dnes]]|publisher=[[Mafra (company)|Mafra]]|date=24 October 2013|access-date=14 December 2022|language=cs}}</ref> The same year on 27 October, he made his [[Bundesliga]] debut in a 0–3 home defeat against [[Hamburger SV]].<ref>{{Cite magazine|title=Baumanns rabenschwarzer Sonntag|url=https://www.kicker.de/freiburg-gegen-hsv-2013-bundesliga-1894962/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|date=27 October 2013|access-date=14 December 2022|language=de}}</ref>

On 2 November 2014, Darida scored a penalty for the only goal of the game away to [[1. FC Köln]] to give the club their first win in their 10th game of the season, moving them out of the direct relegation places.<ref>{{cite news|first=Adam|last=Delicate|title=1.FC Köln 0–1 SC Freiburg: Darida secures SCF's first win|url=http://www.vavel.com/en/international-football/germany-bundesliga/410696-1-fc-koln-0-sc-freiburg-1-report.html|website=Vavel|date=2 November 2014|access-date=4 November 2014}}</ref>

===Hertha BSC===
Darida signed for [[Hertha BSC]] following [[SC Freiburg|Freiburg]]'s relegation ahead of the [[2015–16 Bundesliga]] for an undisclosed fee, wearing number 6 shirt.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Hertha Berlin sign Czech midfielder Vladimir Darida from Freiburg|url=http://www.espnfc.co.uk/story/2527421/hertha-berlin-sign-czech-midfielder-vladimir-darida|url-status=dead|website=[[ESPN]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150719151304/http://www.espnfc.co.uk/story/2527421/hertha-berlin-sign-czech-midfielder-vladimir-darida|archive-date=19 July 2015}}</ref> He made an immediate impact for his club by scoring on his debut in the first round of [[DFB-Pokal]] against [[Arminia Bielefeld]], which ended in a 2–0 victory. Darida got his first assist of the season through setting up [[Salomon Kalou]] in a 3–1 defeat to [[Borussia Dortmund]].<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.espnfc.com/player/165637/vladimir-darida| title = Vladimír Darida Stats, News, Bio {{!}} ESPN}}</ref> On 27 September he got his first league goal of the season scoring the equaliser in a 1–1 draw away to [[Eintracht Frankfurt|Frankfurt]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Eintracht Frankfurt 1–1 Hertha Berlin, Darida salvages point for Dardai's men|url=http://www.fourfourtwo.com/news/eintracht-frankfurt-1-hertha-berlin-1-darida-salvages-point-dardais-men|website=[[FourFourTwo]]|date=27 September 2015}}</ref>

===Aris Thessaloniki===
Darida signed for [[Aris Thessaloniki F.C.|Aris Thessaloniki]] in December 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Povrzeno. Darida do Arisu|url=https://www.sport.cz/clanek/fotbal-bundesliga-povrzeno-darida-do-arisu-3840300|website=[[Seznam.cz|Sport.cz]]|publisher=Borgis|agency=[[Czech News Agency]]|date=14 December 2022|language=cs}}</ref>

===Hradec Králové===
On 23 May 2025, Darida signed a one-year contract with [[FC Hradec Králové|Hradec Králové]] with option.<ref>{{Cite web|title=    Darida se po 12 letech vrací do Česka, posílil Hradec Králové|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/prvni-liga/vladimir-darida-posila-hradec-kralove-aris-solun.A250523_153230_fotbal_ten|newspaper=[[Mladá fronta Dnes]]|publisher=[[Mafra (company)|Mafra]]|agency=[[Czech News Agency]]|date=23 May 2025|access-date=23 May 2025|language=cs}}</ref>

==International career==
On 26 May 2012, Darida debuted for the Czech Republic national football team in a 2–1 [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] victory against [[Israel national football team|Israel]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Jaroslav|last=Beránek|title=Darida jede na Euro místo Pudila! Trenér Bílek už změnu oznámil hráčům|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/euro-2012/nominace-na-fotbalove-euro-misto-pudila-jede-darida.A120527_222113_euro-2012_ber|website=Mladá fronta Dnes|publisher=Mafra|date=27 May 2012|access-date=16 June 2024|language=cs}}</ref> Two days later, he was included in the Czech squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2012]] to replace the injured defender [[Daniel Pudil]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Darida brought into Czech squad|url=http://espnfc.com/euro2012/en/news/1080317/league/UEFA.EURO/season/2012/darida-brought-into-czech-squad.html|website=ESPN|date=28 May 2012|access-date=11 November 2013}}</ref> In the UEFA Euro 2012 quarter-final against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]], Darida earned his second international appearance as well as first in a competitive tournament, replacing the injured [[Tomáš Rosický]] before coming off as a substitute after 61 minutes for [[Jan Rezek]], ending in a 1–0 loss for the Czechs.<ref>{{cite news|first=Tom|last=Rostance|title=Czech Republic 0–1 Portugal|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/18355069|website=[[BBC Sport]]|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=21 June 2012|access-date=4 November 2014}}</ref>

Darida was included in the Czech Republic squad for [[UEFA Euro 2020]],<ref>{{Cite news|title=V nominaci reprezentace na ME chybí Dočkal, Šilhavý čeká na Kúdelu|url=https://www.eurofotbal.cz/clanky/v-nominaci-reprezentace-na-me-chybi-dockal-silhavy-ceka-na-kudelu-502583/|url-status=dead|date=25 May 2021|website=Eurofotbal|language=cs|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210719092050/https://www.eurofotbal.cz/clanky/v-nominaci-reprezentace-na-me-chybi-dockal-silhavy-ceka-na-kudelu-502583/|archive-date=19 July 2021}}</ref> serving as captain,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/euro-2020-czech-republic-captain-borek-dockal-tomas-soucek|title=Euro 2020 – who is Czech Republic captain, Vladimir Darida?|author1=FourFourTwo Staff|date=27 May 2021|website=fourfourtwo.com}}</ref> after which he retired from international football as he wanted to focus on spending time with his family.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Czech Republic captain Darida retires from national team|url=https://eu.usatoday.com/story/sports/soccer/2021/07/04/czech-republic-captain-darida-retires-from-national-team/47061827/|website=[[USA Today]]|date=4 July 2021|access-date=16 June 2024}}</ref> [[Tomáš Souček]] was named as his successor as national team captain.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.denik.cz/fotbal/soucek-si-uziva-dovolenou-a-tesi-se-na-roli-kapitana-mozna-bude-vic-rozhovoru.html|title=Souček si užívá dovolenou a těší se na roli kapitána: Možná bude víc rozhovorů|website=[[Deník]]|date=14 July 2021|access-date=24 August 2021|language=cs|publisher=[[Vltava Labe Media]]}}</ref>

In March 2026, Darida agreed to return to the national team and help the team in [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA second round|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification play-offs]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Velká diplomatická výhra Nedvěda. Přemluvil Daridu, aby znovu navlékl reprezentační dres|url=https://www.efotbal.cz/article/fotbal-mistrovstvi-sveta-velka-diplomaticka-vyhra-nedveda-premluvil-daridu-aby-znovu-navlekl-reprezentacni-dres-fc2a4f30-6084-4489-b9a2-90378d047f62|work=efotbal.cz|language=cs|date=24 February 2026|access-date=17 March 2026}}</ref>

